description:
# Multiple Conditions with Else If

Sometimes you need to check multiple conditions, not just two! That's where **else if** comes in.

## Else If Structure

Check multiple conditions in sequence:

```csharp
int level = 15;

if (level >= 20)
{
    Console.WriteLine("You are a Master!");
}
else if (level >= 10)
{
    Console.WriteLine("You are an Expert!");
}
else if (level >= 5)
{
    Console.WriteLine("You are an Apprentice!");
}
else
{
    Console.WriteLine("You are a Beginner!");
}
```

**How it works:**
- C# checks each condition in order from top to bottom
- The FIRST true condition runs its block
- All remaining conditions are skipped
- If no conditions are true, the else block runs (if present)

## Your Quest

Create a character class system based on stats:
1. Get the player's strength and intelligence values
2. Use else if to determine their class:
   - If strength >= 15 AND intelligence >= 15: "Paladin"
   - Else if strength >= 15: "Warrior"
   - Else if intelligence >= 15: "Mage"
   - Else: "Villager"
3. Print their class with a description
4. Calculate and display their total stat points

starterCode:
using System;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        Console.WriteLine("=== CHARACTER CLASS SELECTOR ===");

        // Get player stats
        Console.Write("Enter your Strength (0-20): ");
        int strength = int.Parse(Console.ReadLine());

        Console.Write("Enter your Intelligence (0-20): ");
        int intelligence = int.Parse(Console.ReadLine());

        // Calculate total stats
        int totalStats = strength + intelligence;

        // Determine class based on stats
        string characterClass;
        string description;

        if (/* strength >= 15 AND intelligence >= 15 */)
        {
            characterClass = "Paladin";
            description = "A holy warrior with balanced combat and magic skills";
        }
        else if (/* strength >= 15 */)
        {
            characterClass = "Warrior";
            description = "A powerful melee fighter";
        }
        else if (/* intelligence >= 15 */)
        {
            characterClass = "Mage";
            description = "A master of arcane magic";
        }
        else
        {
            characterClass = "Villager";
            description = "A humble commoner with potential to grow";
        }

        // Display results
        Console.WriteLine($"\nYour class: {characterClass}");
        Console.WriteLine($"Description: {description}");
        Console.WriteLine($"Total stat points: {totalStats}");
    }
}

solutionCode:
using System;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        Console.WriteLine("=== CHARACTER CLASS SELECTOR ===");

        // Get player stats
        Console.Write("Enter your Strength (0-20): ");
        int strength = int.Parse(Console.ReadLine());

        Console.Write("Enter your Intelligence (0-20): ");
        int intelligence = int.Parse(Console.ReadLine());

        // Calculate total stats
        int totalStats = strength + intelligence;

        // Determine class based on stats
        string characterClass;
        string description;

        if (strength >= 15 && intelligence >= 15)
        {
            characterClass = "Paladin";
            description = "A holy warrior with balanced combat and magic skills";
        }
        else if (strength >= 15)
        {
            characterClass = "Warrior";
            description = "A powerful melee fighter";
        }
        else if (intelligence >= 15)
        {
            characterClass = "Mage";
            description = "A master of arcane magic";
        }
        else
        {
            characterClass = "Villager";
            description = "A humble commoner with potential to grow";
        }

        // Display results
        Console.WriteLine($"\nYour class: {characterClass}");
        Console.WriteLine($"Description: {description}");
        Console.WriteLine($"Total stat points: {totalStats}");
    }
}
